<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 27 at 12:22AM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...CAUTIOUS TRAVEL IS ADVISED FOR REDUCED VISIBILITY IN FOG EARLY
THIS MORNING...
WEATHER...
* Patchy dense fog will impact portions of southeastern Michigan
during the early morning hours. A few areas will likely observe
visibilities of one quarter mile or less.
IMPACTS...
* The most favored areas for locally dense fog will be in the
higher elevation of the Irish Hills and areas adjacent to Lake
Huron, St Clair River and Lake St Clair.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Patchy fog means areas coverage or duration of the fog will
be limited. Motorists are urged to use caution and account
for variable driving conditions by slowing down and allowing
extra time.
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
